<subSubSection id="DDE53EF8FF82FA482700F881FB976397" pageId="3" pageNumber="195" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="95406D73FF82FA482700F881FB976397" blockId="3.[833,1504,1345,1978]" pageId="3" pageNumber="195">
Distribution and biodiversity hotspot: Western Argentina in the provinces of La Rioja and Mendoza (
<figureCitation id="0DC471F6FF82FA4820CBF865FB4463B3" box="[1195,1261,1931,1950]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[114,141,1296,1310]" captionTargetBox="[329,1289,149,1265]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[329,1289,149,1265]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 27. Map of South America with elevational relief and biodiversity hotspots (in grey) showing distribution of Plyomydas adelphe sp. nov. (orange), P. peruviensis (yellow), and P. phalaros sp. nov. (blue). Type localities plotted with square symbols. Map data available in Google Earth KML file 6102and also through GBIF (data-set 7f2de377-9f9f-4276-b0b8-5c792b499223, DOI 10.15468/tiymja)." pageId="3" pageNumber="195">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Not known to occur in any biodiversity hotspot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
