<subSubSection id="DDE53EF8FF85FA4F2415FC3EFDD2607F" pageId="4" pageNumber="196" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="95406D73FF85FA4F2415FC3EFDD2607F" blockId="4.[85,756,976,1106]" pageId="4" pageNumber="196">
Remarks: Sexual dimorphism is minimal. Based on the three known specimens, females are larger (wing length 
<quantity id="5207C096FF85FA4F263BFC02FD1A67D2" box="[603,691,1004,1023]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="4" pageNumber="196" unit="mm" value="18.5">18.5 mm</quantity>
