<typeStatus id="4A44D3D1FF85FA4F24B8FBE6FE9D6036" box="[216,308,1032,1051]" pageId="4" pageNumber="196">paratype</typeStatus>
, 
<quantity id="5207C096FF85FA4F2522FBE6FE7B6036" box="[322,466,1032,1051]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.59" metricValueMax="1.66" metricValueMin="1.52" pageId="4" pageNumber="196" unit="mm" value="15.9" valueMax="16.6" valueMin="15.2">15.2–16.6 mm</quantity>
in two males) and dimorphism only occurs in color of legs and sclerites. The 
<typeStatus id="4A44D3D1FF85FA4F260BFBCAFD6C601A" box="[619,709,1060,1079]" pageId="4" pageNumber="196">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in low flat mesquite desert and dry riverbed.
</paragraph>
